Scottish First Minister Nicola Sturgeon refused to rule out a second independence vote .
But she insisted an SNP victory in the General Election would not trigger a second vote if the SNP wins the 2016 Holyrood elections .
A poll by Ipsos Mori reveals that a referendum on EU membership was more popular with voters north of the border than another independence ballot .
The most popular policy was increasing the minimum wage for those over 21 .